summaries.short: Margene befriends Bill's potential fourth wife; a dangerous polygamist family accuses Bill of poaching.
summaries.full: Having uncovered Bill's romantic secret, Margene befriends an unsuspecting Ana, then arranges lunch with Barb and Nicki to introduce them to their prospective sister-wife. Bill tries to get a reluctant Don to embrace his Weber Gaming deal; and he discovers that an underground polygamist group, the Greenes, have resurfaced with a vengeance.

summaries.short: Margene's mother visits the Henricksons; Roman's rivals force Bill to play a dangerous game.
summaries.full: Margene's dysfunctional past is illuminated when her mother Ginger pays a visit to the Henricksons. With tensions at a fever pitch as federal agents close in on the fugitive polygamist leader Orlean Abbot, Bill plays a dangerous end-game to land Weber Gaming, pitting Roman against the Greenes and vice-versa.

summaries.short: Bill meets a romantic prospect; Nicki frets over Wayne's school lessons; Bill turns to Eddie for a loan.
summaries.full: Discussing his sideline business with Don over lunch at a local diner, Bill finds himself drawn to an attractive young waitress named Ana. Nicki worries over Wayne's enrollment at a Catholic school. At Home Plus, Bill finds his deal with Weber Gaming jeopardized by Reese's impatience and must turn to his uncle Eddie for a loan.

summaries.short: Bill proposes a 'seventh day off' schedule to his wives, and cons Roman into retaliating against the Greenes.
summaries.full: Stressed out from the Weber deal and exhausted by Margene's sexual appetite, Bill proposes that he take a night off from the wives every seventh day. With the Weber deal still in doubt, Bill continues to play both sides of the inter-compound dispute, hoping to incite Roman to take retaliatory measures that will finish off the Greenes.

summaries.short: Bill eyes a new polygamy-friendly business; Rhonda complicates Nicki's involvement in Joey's case.
summaries.full: Bill's anxieties over his upcoming testimony in Joey's case are compounded by Rhonda, who threatens to blackmail Nicki into letting her stay with the Henricksons. Looking to provide long-term security for his family in the face of uncertainty, Bill, along with Don and Eddie, meets with Carter Reese, owner of a polygamy-friendly slot-machine business.

summaries.short: Margene finds herself wielding a swing vote; Rhonda stays in the spotlight; Lois reaches out to Bill.
summaries.full: Bill enlists Nicki to sell Barb and Margene on Weber Gaming, with predictable results. In the wake of the latest public blemish on Juniper Creek, Bill calls an emergency UEB meeting that Alby ends up crashing. Burned by Frank, a distraught Lois fights to get back into Bill's good graces, and turns to an unexpected source for advice.

summaries.short: Bill tries to leverage a council vote against Roman; Barb chastens Margene for her relationship with Ben.
summaries.full: Bill tries to leverage a council vote against Roman. Arriving at Lois's cabin, they are surprised to find her brother Eddie overseeing Lois's new laundromat investment. At home, Barb catches Ben in a compromising position with Margene. At the compound, Alby refuses to toe the party line. Bill discusses a radical, polygamy-proof business option with Don.
